        "content": "<p>Thanks! I misunderstood how to use <code>set_option pp.all</code>. With this command, I can now obtain the verbose <code>pp.all</code> form:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">natDegree</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extract_goal</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>After reading the comments in <code>Mathlib/Tactic/ExtractGoal.lean</code>, it appears that it’s well known that <code>extract_goal</code> sometimes fails to pretty-print the goal in a round-trippable, equivalent way.</p>",
        "id": 501809846,
        "sender_full_name": "Isak Colboubrani",
        "timestamp": 1740491163
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, striking a balance between round-tripping and conciseness/legibility is hard!</p>",
        "id": 501813956,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1740492270
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In general, you should expect <code>extract_goal</code> to work unless there are some coercions.  In some cases, <code>pp.analize</code> is a good compromise between no option and <code>pp.all</code>, but that may fail (as I think it does in this case).</p>",
        "id": 501814145,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1740492326
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>pp.all</code> is expected to always work (although I have a vague memory that even that can get confused sometimes).</p>",
        "id": 501814269,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1740492356
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"321459\">Damiano Testa</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/.60extract_goal.60.20round-trip/near/501814269\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>pp.all</code> is expected to always work (although I have a vague memory that even that can get confused sometimes).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I can confirm that there are (or were) cases where it does not work</p>",
        "id": 501814708,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1740492457
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"321459\">@Damiano Testa</span>! It appears that using <code>by set_option pp.analyze true in extract_goal</code> produces the same results as <code>by extract_goal</code> for these four test cases.</p>",
        "id": 501819041,
        "sender_full_name": "Isak Colboubrani",
        "timestamp": 1740493535
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Update: I attempted round-tripping using <code>by set_option pp.all true in extract_goal</code> for all five test cases.</p>\n<p>Round-tripping (<code>pp.all</code>) failed for these two cases:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">//</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extract_goal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- solvable by aesop</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extract_goal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- solvable by decide</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>However, it appears to have worked for these three cases:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">natDegree</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">])</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extract_goal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- solvable by compute_degree</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extract_goal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- solvable by norm_num</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">126432</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ZMod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1235412223</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">12355342321</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1001528716</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extract_goal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- solvable by reduce_mod_char</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Let me know if any of these cases are worth opening an issue for.</p>",
        "id": 501822339,
        "sender_full_name": "Isak Colboubrani",
        "timestamp": 1740494380
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You need <code>extract_goal *</code></p>",
        "id": 501827181,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1740495636
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Doh! I naively assumed the behavior of <code>extract_goal *</code> was the <code>extract_goal</code> default. Thanks!</p>\n<p>That solved the <code>aesop</code> <code>pp.all</code> round-trip which is nice.</p>\n<p>However, I'm still unable to get the <code>decide</code> <code>pp.all</code> round-trip to work despite using <code>extract_goal *</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">set_option</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pp</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">extract_goal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- solvable by decide</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 501830574,
        "sender_full_name": "Isak Colboubrani",
        "timestamp": 1740496514
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You need to insert a <code>revert m</code> in the extracted proof</p>",
        "id": 501830887,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1740496592
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>extract_goal</code> implicitly does <code>intros</code></p>",
        "id": 501830930,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1740496605
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"310045\">@Eric Wieser</span>, everything works now.</p>\n<p>Out of curiosity, what is the rationale behind having <code>extract_goal</code> implicitly perform <code>intros</code>? I had naively assumed that using <code>extract_goal</code> would preserve the goal exactly as it is—or at least as closely as possible.</p>",
        "id": 501886999,
        "sender_full_name": "Isak Colboubrani",
        "timestamp": 1740509570
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>extract_goal</code> makes use of the standard signature pretty printer (what <code>#check</code> uses).</p>\n<p>Here's how to think of the steps (though it's not literally this): it does <code>revert</code> to all the hypotheses, and then it uses the signature pretty printer on the resulting type.</p>",
        "id": 501977136,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1740554232
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Doing <code>intros</code> automatically is partially justified by the fact that theorems in mathlib shouldn't usually start with <code>intro</code>. Instead, the theorem statement should be modified to put the hypotheses before the colon.</p>",
        "id": 501977385,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1740554357
    }
]